---
import Layout from "../components/layout/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="About"
  description="What Open Ordinal is, why it exists, and who runs it."
  lang="en"
  canonical="https://openordinal.org/about"
>
  <section class="archive-shell entry-prose">
    <h1 class="text-[46px] leading-tight text-ink">About</h1>

    <p>Open Ordinal is a bilingual research archive of structured economic and social data analysis focused on Africa.</p>

    <h2>Why it exists</h2>
    <p>Most data about African economies and societies is scattered, inconsistently sourced, or buried in reports few people read. Open Ordinal exists to surface it in one place &mdash; dated, reproducible, and honest about its own limits.</p>

    <h2>What you will find</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Dated entries with clear scope, dataset references, and source links</li>
      <li>Chart-led analysis with caveats and limitations documented in plain language</li>
      <li>Reusable data assets released under open licenses</li>
      <li>Bilingual publication in English and French</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Editorial stance</h2>
    <p>Open Ordinal prioritizes traceability over certainty. We document what the data can support, what it cannot, and where gaps remain.</p>

    <h2>Ownership and contact</h2>
    <p>Open Ordinal is a project of Utopia UGX Group Ltd.</p>

    <p>
      Open Ordinal contact: <a href="mailto:hello@openordinal.org">hello@openordinal.org</a><br />
      Utopia Group contact: <a href="mailto:hello@utopiagroup.io">hello@utopiagroup.io</a>
    </p>

    <p>
      Utopia UGX Group website:
      <a href="https://utopiagroup.io" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">https://utopiagroup.io</a>
    </p>
  </section>
</Layout>
